Eye-Tracking Eye-Region Image Dataset License
Version 1.0

Copyright (c) 2026 [Shukun Li, BIT.IFE]

1. Scope

This dataset consists of cropped eye-region images derived from eye-tracking experiments conducted under institutional ethical approval. 
All facial regions outside the eye area have been removed. 
No direct identifiers (e.g., name, ID number, contact information) are included.

2. Permitted Use

The dataset is provided solely for non-commercial academic research and educational purposes.

Users are permitted to:
- Use the dataset for scientific research
- Publish results derived from the dataset
- Modify and process the dataset for research purposes

3. Restrictions

Users may NOT:
- Use the dataset for commercial purposes
- Redistribute the raw dataset to third parties
- Attempt to re-identify any individual
- Use the dataset for biometric identification systems
- Use the dataset to train commercial face or iris recognition systems

4. Data Sharing

The dataset may not be redistributed in its original form. 
Researchers wishing to access the dataset must obtain it directly from the original authors and agree to these license terms.

5. Attribution Requirement

Any publication or work using this dataset must cite:

[Full citation of your paper]

6. No Warranty

The dataset is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. 
The authors and affiliated institution assume no responsibility for misuse of the data.

7. Ethical Compliance

Users agree to comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and institutional review requirements in their jurisdiction.

By downloading or using this dataset, you agree to the terms of this license.
